Construction of 7000 Piezometers and installation of DWLRS with telemetry in OE, Critical, Semi-Critical assessment units and other priority areas

Creation of infrastructure for automated monitoring of water levels in water stressed assessment units. High frequency data would also provide scientific inputs for driving corrective action by State/Central agencies based on ground water level monitoring system. High density and high frequency water level data would form a critical input to water budgeting and planning for ground water interventions at the Panchayat level in such areas and in improved assessment of groundwater resources.
Heli-borne surveys for high resolution mapping in ~3 lakh sq km area in arid parts of NW India

High Resolution mapping of aquifers on 1:10,000 scale in arid parts of the country will help formulate better ground water management plans. Will help provide Pin-pointed sites and depth zones for taking up appropriate management interventions for water harvesting and recharge in water stressed areas.
Data Generation for Aquifer Mapping through construction of Wells in 11 States

Construction of 1135 wells for data generation for completing remaining works of Aquifer Mapping on 1:50,000 scale. Improved information about aquifer disposition, quantification of available ground water resources and assessment of groundwater quality.
